('744', '1', '2018-10-16 00:41:23', '2018-10-15 22:41:23', 'Roberto Cuoghi (Modena, 1973). Lives and works in Milan, Italy\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>SOLO EXHIBITIONS</h2>\r\n<strong>2017</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi: Perla Pollina, 1996–2016</em>, Centre d’Art Contemporain Genève, Geneva, Switzerland, February 22 – April 30, 2017, curated by Andrea Bellini.\r\n[Traveling to Madre – Museo d’arte contemporanea Donnaregina, Naples, Italy, May 15 – September 11, 2017].\r\n\r\n<em>Imitazione di Cristo (Imitation of Christ)</em>; “Il Mondo Magico” (The Magical World), Italian Pavilion, 57° Biennale di Venezia, Venice, Italy, May 13 – November 26, curated by Cecilia Alemani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2016</strong>\r\n<em>Putiferio</em>, DESTE Foundation Project Space, Slaughterhouse, Hydra, Greece, June 21 – September 30, 2016.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2014</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi: Suillakku Corral</em>, New Museum, New York, USA, April 30 – June 29, 2014, curated by Massimiliano Gioni and Margot Norton.\r\n\r\n<em>Da iḍā e piṅgalā a iḍā e iḍā o piṅgalā e piṅgalā</em>, Le Consortium, centre d’art, Dijon, France, October 17, 2014 – January 11, 2015.\r\n[Traveled to Aspen Art Museum, Aspen, USA, February 13 – May 31, 2015].\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2012</strong>\r\n<em>ZOLOTO</em>, Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, May 30 – July 13, 2012.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2011</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi</em>, UCLA Hammer Museum, Los Angeles, USA, January 22 – May 15, 2011, curated by Ali Subotnick.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2008</strong>\r\n<em>Suillakku</em>, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, May 6 – July 27, 2008, curated by M. Beccaria.\r\n[Traveled to ICA – Institute of Contemporary Arts, London, UK, October 14 – November 23, 2008].\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2007\r\n</strong><em>Roberto Cuoghi: Mei Gui</em>, Centre International d’Art et du Paysage de l’Île de Vassivière, Beaumont du Lac, France, January 17, 2007. Presented in the context of Un million et quarante-quatrième anniversaire de l’art / 1 000 044 candles for art, held on January 17 in various venues throughout France.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2006</strong>\r\n<em>Mei Gui</em>, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 22 – October 4, 2006.\r\n\r\n<em>Mbube</em>, objectif_exhibitions, Antwerp, Belgium, October 26 – November 25, 2006, curated by Tommy Simoens.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\n<em>The Wrong Gallery</em>, New York, USA, March 7–30, 2005, curated by Maurizio Cattelan, Massimiliano Gioni, and Ali Subotnick.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2003</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi: Foolish Things</em>, Eldorado project room, GAMeC – Galleria d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, February 9 – March 30, 2003, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio and Alessandro Rabottini.\r\n\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi</em>, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 29 – October 30, 2003.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>1997</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi / Alberta Pellacani</em>, Spazio Aperto, GAM – Galleria d’Arte Moderna di Bologna, Bologna, Italy, December 19, 1997 – January 7, 1998, curated by Walter Guadagnini and Dede Auregli.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>GROUP EXHIBITIONS</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2018</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Sanguine. Luc Tuymans on Baroque</em>, Fondazione Prada, Milan, Italy, October 16 2018 - February 25 2019.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2016</strong>\r\n<em>Exquisite Corpse</em>, The Mistake Room, Los Angeles, USA, May 14 – July 2, 2016, curated by Niklas Svennung.\r\n\r\n<em>My Blueberry Night</em>, Residenza Casarotto di Albegno, Albegno di Treviolo (Bergamo), Italy, May 16, 2016, curated by Antonio Grulli, organized by Club GAMeC.\r\n\r\n<em>Curated by (?)</em>, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, June 30 – October 16, 2016\r\n\r\n<em>Versus: La sfida dell’artista al suo modello in un secolo di fotografia e disegno</em>, Galleria civica di Modena, Modena, Italy, September 16, 2016 – January 8, 2017, curated by Andrea Bruciati, Daniele De Luigi and Serena Goldoni.\r\n\r\n<em>Ether</em>, Galerie Chantal Crousel, Paris, France, October 15 – November 19, 2016.\r\n\r\n<em>A occhi chiusi, gli occhi sono straordinariamente aperti</em>, XVI Quadriennale d’arte, Palazzo delle Esposizioni, Rome, Italy, October 13, 2016 – January 8, 2017, curated by Luca Lo Pinto.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2015</strong>\r\n<em>Fobofilia: Opere dalla Collezione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo</em>, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, February 12 – April 12, 2015, curated by Irene Calderoni.\r\n\r\n<em>Future Season Past</em>, Lehmann Maupin, New York, USA, February 28 – April 18, 2015, curated by Manuel E. Gonzalez.\r\n\r\n<em>Liberi Tutti! Arte e società in Italia 1989–2001</em>, Museo Ettore Fico, Turin, Italy, July 9 – October 18, 2015, curated by Luca Beatrice, Andrea Busto, and Cristiana Perrella.\r\n\r\n<em>Spin-Off: Muestra de la Colección Sandretto Re Rebaudengo</em>, Centro de Arte Contemporáneo de Quito, Montevideo y Luis Dàvila, Quito, Ecuador, August 1 – November 30, 2015.\r\n\r\n<em>Ennesima: Una mostra di sette mostre sull’arte italiana / An Exhibition of Seven Exhibitions on Italian Art</em>, Triennale di Milano, Milan, Italy, November 26, 2015 – March 6, 2016, curated by Vincenzo de Bellis.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2014</strong>\r\n<em>Ritratto dell’artista da giovane / Portrait of the Artist as a Young (Wo)Man</em>, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, June 10 – September 21, 2014, curated by Marcella Beccaria.\r\n\r\n<em>Per formare una collezione #3</em>, Madre – Museo d’arte contemporanea Donnaregina, Naples, Italy, October 11, 2014 – in progress, curated by Alessandro Rabottini and Eugenio Viola.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2013</strong>\r\n<em>Große Gefühle: Von der Antike bis zur Gegenwart / Deep Feelings: From Antiquity to Now</em>, Kunsthalle Krems, Krems, Austria, March 10 – June 30, 2013, curated by Brigitte Borchhardt-Birbaumer, Irene Calderoni, Sylvia Ferino-Pagden, and Hans-Peter Wipplinger.\r\n\r\n<em>The System of Objects: The Dakis Joannou Collection reloaded by Andreas Angelidakis</em>, DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece, May 15 – November 30, 2013, curated by Andreas Angelidakis and Maria Cristina Didero.\r\n\r\n<em>Bestiario contemporaneo: Fra arte e scienze, gli artisti italiani della collezione ACACIA / A Contemporary Bestiary: Between Art and Science, Italian Artists of the ACACIA</em> <em>Collection</em>, Museo di Storia Naturale, Venice, Italy, May 31 – October 24, 2013, curated by Gemma De Angelis Testa and Giorgio Verzotti.\r\n\r\n<em>Il Palazzo Enciclopedico / The Encyclopedic Palace</em>, 55a Esposizione Internazionale d’Arte La Biennale di Venezia, Venice, Italy, June 1 – November 24, 2013, curated by Massimiliano Gioni.\r\n\r\n<em>Collection Sandretto Re Rebaudengo: Have you seen me before?</em>, Whitechapel Gallery, London, UK, June 18 – September 8, 2013, curated by Achim Borchardt-Hume and Francesco Bonami. The exhibition is part of the series Think Twice: Twenty Years of Contemporary Art from Collection Sandretto Re Rebaudengo.\r\n\r\n<em>Out of the Blue</em>, Cortesi Gallery, Lugano, Switzerland, October 11 – December 20, 2013, curated by Alberto Salvadori.\r\n\r\n<em>Intenzione manifesta: Il disegno in tutte le sue forme / Manifest Intention: Drawing in All Its Forms</em>, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, October 11, 2013 – January 25, 2014, curated by Beatrice Merz and Marianna Vecellio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2012</strong>\r\n<em>Print/Out: 20 Years in Prints</em>, Museum of Modern Art, New York, USA, February 19 – May 14, 2012, curated by Christophe Cherix.\r\n\r\n<em>Gli artisti italiani della Collezione ACACIA / The Italian Artists of the ACACIA Collection</em>, Palazzo nReale, Milan, Italy, April 12 – June 24, 2012, curated by Gemma De Angelis Testa and Giorgio Verzotti.\r\n\r\n<em>The Residue of Memory</em>, Aspen Art Museum, Aspen, USA, May 11 – July 15, 2012, curated by Heidi Zuckerman.\r\n\r\n<em>These Peanuts are Bullets</em>, Family Business, New York, USA, July 10–14, 2012, organized by Le Dictateur.\r\n\r\n<em>Fuoriclasse: Vent’anni di arte italiana nei corsi di Alberto Garutti</em>, GAM – Galleria d’Arte Moderna, Milan, October 7 – December 9, 2012, curated by Luca Cerizza.\r\n\r\n<em>Marco Colombaioni: I quadri di Annibale</em>, Museo di Storia Naturale, Milan, Italy, December 7, 2012 – January 13, 2013.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2010</strong>\r\n<em>Skin Fruit: Selections from the Dakis Joannou Collection</em>, New Museum, New York, USA, March 3 – June 6, 2010, curated by Jeff Koons.\r\n\r\n<em>Ibrido: Genetica delle forme d’arte</em>, PAC – Padiglione d’Arte Contemporanea, Milan, Italy, March 13–31, 2010, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio and Francesco Garutti.\r\n\r\n<em>HaVE A LoOk! Have a Look!</em>, FormContent, London, UK, May 7 – July 11, 2010.\r\n\r\n<em>Alpha Omega: Works from the Dakis Joannou Collection</em>, DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece, June 16 – December 29, 2010, curated by Massimiliano Gioni and Dakis Joannou.\r\n\r\n<em>Barbaric Freedom</em>, Simon Lee Gallery, London, UK, July 9 – September 11, 2010, curated by Anne Pontegnie.\r\n\r\n<em>10000 Lives</em>, The 8th Gwangju Biennale, Gwangju, South Korea, September 3 – November 7, 2010, curated by Massimiliano Gioni.\r\n\r\n<em>Il Museo Privato: La passione per l’arte contemporanea nelle collezioni bergamasche</em>, GAMeC – Galleria d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, October 6, 2010 – February 14, 2011, curated by Giacinto di Pietrantonio and Maria Cristina Rodeschini.\r\n\r\n<em>Club 21: Remaking the Scene</em>, One Marylebone, London, UK, October 13–23, 2010, curated by Oxana Maleeva and Steve Piccolo.\r\n\r\n<em>Hareng Saur: Ensor en de hedendaagse kunst / Hareng Saur: Ensor and Contemporary Art</em>, Museum voor Schone Kunsten &amp; S.M.A.K., Ghent, Belgium, October 31, 2010 – February 27, 2011, curated by Johan De Smet and Ronald Van de Sompel.\r\n\r\n<em>Plus Ultra: Opere dalla Collezione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo</em>, MACRO Testaccio, Rome, Italy, December 17, 2010 – March 20, 2011, curated by Francesco Bonami.\r\n\r\n<em>Espíritu y espacio / Spirit and Space: Collección Sandretto Re Rebaudengo</em>, Sala de Arte Santander, Boadilla del Monte, Madrid, Spain, February 9 – May 15, 2011, curated by Francesco Bonami, organized by Fundación Banco Santander and Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo.\r\n\r\n<em>La collezione della Galleria Civica di Modena: Fotografie e disegni dalle Raccolte</em>, Galleria civica di Modena, Modena, Italy, April 2 – July 17, 2011.\r\n\r\n<em>Surreal versus Surrealismo en el arte contemporáneo</em>, IVAM Institut Valencià d’Art Modern, Valencia, Spain, October 6 – January 8, 2011, curated by Gianni Mercurio and Demetrio Paparoni.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2009</strong>\r\n<em>Esposizione Universale: L’arte alla prova del tempo / In the Time of Art: Masterpieces from the 16th to the 21st Century</em>, GaMeC – Galleria d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, April 3 – July 26, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio.\r\n[Traveled to Fundación PROA, Buenos Aires, Argentina, September 19, 2009 – January 10, 2010: El Tiempo del Arte: Obras Maestras del Siglo XVI al XXI].\r\n\r\n<em>The PIG presents 8 Solo Shows...</em>, Deitch Projects, New York, USA, April 25 – August 9, 2009, curated by Gelitin.\r\n\r\n<em>The Uncertainty Principle</em>, Capella MACBA, Barcelona, Spain, May 15 – June 12, 2009.\r\n\r\n<em>Fare Mondi / Making Worlds</em>, 53a Esposizione Internazionale d’Arte La Biennale di Venezia, Venice, Italy, June 7 – November 22, 2009, curated by Daniel Birnbaum.\r\n\r\n<em>World Question Center</em>, in Heaven, 2nd Athens Biennale, various venues, Athens, Greece, June 15 – October 4, 2009, curated by Chus Martínez.\r\n\r\n<em>Indagini di un cane: Opere d’arte di cinque fondazioni europee / Investigations of a Dog: Works from Five European Art Foundations</em>, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, October 21 – Febuary 7, 2010, curated by Francesco Bonami and Irene Calderoni.\r\n[Traveled to Ellipse Foundation, Cascais, Portugal, May 15 – September 5, 2010, curated by Alexandre Melo; La maison rouge – Fondation Antoine de Galbert, Paris, France, October 23, 2010 – January 15, 2011, curated by Noelig Le Roux; Magasin 3 Stockholm Konsthall, Stockholm, Sweden, February 17 – May 29, 2011, curated by Tessa Praun; DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece, June 22 – October 15, 2011, curated by Nadja Argyropoulou.]\r\n\r\n<em>Thanksgiving</em>, <em>Peep-Hole Annual Benefit</em>, Peep-Hole, Milan, Italy, November 27 – December 12, 2009.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2008</strong>\r\n<em>Electronic Lounge: La Donazione Halevim al Museo del Novecento</em>, Aeroporto Malpensa, Terminal 1, Milan, Italy, February 27 – May 28, 2008, curated by Edoardo Gnemmi and Iolanda Ratti.\r\n\r\n<em>L’Alchimia dell’Arte Contemporanea: Opere dalla Collezione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo / L’Alchimie de l’Art Contemporain: Œuvres de la Collection Sandretto Re Rebaudengo</em>, Centro Saint-Bénin, Aosta, Italy, May 30 – October 5, 2008.\r\n\r\n<em>The Great Transformation: Kunst und Taktische Magie</em>, Frankfurter Kunstverein, Frankfurt, Germany, June 7 – September 7, 2008, curated by Chus Martínez.\r\n[Traveled to MARCO, Museo de Arte Contemporánea de Vigo, Spain, September 19, 2008 – January 11, 2009: A grande transformación: Arte e maxia táctica].\r\n\r\n<em>Mediterraneo 2008: Perna Foundation</em>, Villa Rufolo, Ravello (Salerno), Italy, June 27 – August 24, 2008, curated by Manuela Annibali.\r\n\r\n<em>Tarantula</em>, Piazza del Duomo, Milan, Italy, June 30 – July 27, 2008. Video program organized by Fondazione Nicola Trussardi and MIA – Milano in Alto, curated by Massimiliano Gioni.\r\n\r\n<em>Pretty Ugly</em>, Gavin Brown’s Enterprise &amp; Maccarone, New York, USA, July 10 – August 29, 2008, curated by Alison M. Gingeras.\r\nAfter Nature, New Museum, New York, USA, July 17 – October 5, 2008, curated by Massimiliano Gioni.\r\n\r\n<em>Noleftovers</em>, Kunsthalle Bern, Bern, Switzerland, August 16 – September 10, 2008. Benefit Auction Preview.\r\n\r\n<em>Italics: Arte Italiana fra Tradizione e Rivoluzione 1968–2008</em>, Palazzo Grassi, Venice, Italy, September 27, 2008 – March 22, 2009, curated by Francesco Bonami.\r\n[Traveled to the Museum of Contemporary Art, Chicago, USA, November 14, 2009 – February 14, 2010: Italics: Italian Art between Tradition and Revolution 1968–2009].\r\n\r\n<em>... And Back Again</em>, presented by PIG, seven solo shows by Alfredo Jaar, Mario Grubisic, Paola Pivi, Gelitin, Jeremy Deller, Simon Martin, and Roberto Cuoghi, Galerie Emmanuel Perrotin, Miami, USA, December 2, 2008 – January 11, 2009.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2007</strong>\r\n<em>Our Magic Hour: European artists’ show</em>, Arario Gallery, Cheonan, South Korea, January 26 – March 11, 2007, curated by Milovan Farronato.\r\n\r\n<em>I Want to Believe</em>, Galerie Eva Presenhuber, Zurich, Switzerland, March 3 – April 7, 2007, curated by Milovan Farronato.\r\n\r\n<em>Dalla terra alla luna: Metafore di viaggio (parte I e II) / From the Earth to the Moon: Metaphors for Travel (Part I and II)</em>, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, April 4 – August 26, 2007, curated by Marcella Beccaria.\r\n\r\n<em>Sequence 1: Pittura e scultura nella Collezione François Pinault / Sequence 1: Peinture et sculpture dans la Collection François Pinault</em>, Palazzo Grassi, Venice, Italy, May 5 – November 11, 2007, curated by Alison M. Gingeras.\r\n\r\n<em>Où? Scènes du Sud: Espagne, Italie, Portugal</em>, Carré d’Art – Musée d’Art Contemporain de Nîmes, Nîmes, France, May 23 – September 23, 2007, curated by Françoise Coh