 Antonio d’Avossa and Centro Arte a Parte. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>1999</strong>\r\nFine, Studio Armin Linke, Milan, Italy, May 31 – June 18, 1999, curated by Lorenzo Silvan. Catalogue.\r\nGuarene Arte 99, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo per l’Arte, September 25 – November 7, 1999, Guarene d’Alba (Cuneo), Italy, selected by Emanuela De Cecco. Catalogue.\r\nIn Camera Caritatis, Globale Positionen 10, Museum in Progress, Vienna, Austria, curated by Massimiliano Gioni.\r\n\r\n<strong>2000</strong>\r\n3nds: Milano, Salara, Bologna, Italy, May 19 – June 13, 2000, curated by Alessandra Galasso and Gianfranco Maraniello. Catalogue.\r\nFuori Uso 2000. The Bridges: Art on the highway / Arte in autostrada, Lungo fiume sud, Pescara, Italy, July 2–19, 2000, curated by Helena Kontova, Emanuela De Cecco, Hou Hanru, and Andreas Schlaegel &amp; Angela Rosenberg. Catalogue.\r\nFai da te / The Amateur View, Sparwasser HQ, Berlin, Germany, December 8, 2000 – January, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza.\r\n\r\n<strong>2001</strong>\r\nPrimo piano: Su la testa! Opere e argomenti in scena, Palazzo delle Papesse Centro Arte Contemporanea, Siena, Italy, February 4–11, 2001, curated by Sergio Risaliti.\r\nMagic and Loss in Pandæmonium: Biennial of Moving Images 2001, The Lux Centre, London, UK, March 2 – April 8, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza and Cristiana Perrella. Catalogue.\r\n[The exhibition was also presented at Artistinvetrina, Fendissime, Rome, Italy, March 2–6, 2001, in collaboration with The British School at Rome; CAC Contemporary Art Centre, Vilnius, Lithuania, March 21 – April 15, 2001: Magic &amp; Loss: Video by young Italian artists, MAN – Museo d’Arte Provincia di Nuoro, Nuoro, Italy, April 6 – May 6, 2001: Magic and Loss: Contemporary Italian Video.]\r\nPlay &gt;, Openspace, Milan, Italy, March 28 – April 29, 2001, curated by Gigiotto del Vecchio. Catalogue.\r\nEspresso: Arte oggi in Italia, Manifattura Tabacchi, Florence, Italy, June 10 – July 20, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza and Gianfranco Maraniello. The exhibition was part of Boom!, a program of five exhibitions curated by Sergio Risaliti.\r\nIl dono: Offerta, ospitalità, insidia / The Gift: Generous Offerings, Threatening Hospitality, Palazzo delle Papesse Centro Arte Contemporanea, Siena, Italy, June 2 – September 23, 2001, curated by Gianfranco Maraniello, Sergio Risaliti, and Antonio Somaini, organized by ICI – Independent Curators International. Catalogue.\r\n[Traveled to Centro Culturale Candiani, Mestre (Venice), Italy, October 14, 2001 – January 6, 2002; Scottsdale Museum of Contemporary Art, Scottsdale, USA, February 7 – May 5, 2002; Bronx Museum of the Arts, Bronx, USA, November 27, 2002 – March 2, 2003; Mary and Leigh Block Museum of Art, Northwestern University, Evanston, USA, April 4 – June 22, 2003; Art Gallery of Hamilton, Hamilton, Canada, August 9 – October 18, 2003.]\r\nVideorom in The 1st Valencia Biennial: Communication between the Arts, various venues, Valencia, Spain, June 13 – October 20, 2001, curated by Cristiana Perrella. Catalogue.\r\nThe End of All Things, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, from June 20, 2001.\r\nTirana Biennale 1: Escape, National Gallery and Chinese Pavilion, Tirana, Albania, September 15 – October 15, 2001, invited by Jens Hoffmann. Catalogue.\r\nIn fumo: Arte, fumetto, comunicazione / In fumo: Art, comics, communication, GAMeC – Galleria\r\nd’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea di Bergamo, Bergamo, Italy, September 27, 2001 – January 6,\r\n2002, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2002</strong>\r\nManifesta 4: European Biennial of Contemporary Art, various venues, Frankfurt, Germany, May 25 – August 25, 2002, curated by Iara Boubnova, Nuria Enguita Mayo, and Stéphanie Moisdon Trembley. Catalogue.\r\nVerso il futuro: Identità nell’arte italiana 1990–2002, Museo del Corso, Rome, Italy, June 26 – August 25, 2002, curated by Costantino D’Orazio and Ludovico Pratesi. Catalogue.\r\nExIt: Nuove geografie della creatività italiana, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, September 21, 2002 – January 6, 2003, curated by Francesco Bonami.\r\nPolyphonix 40, Centre Georges Pompidou, Paris, France, October 1–10, 2002, curated by Manuela Corti. Catalogue.\r\nVideoROM 4.0, ex Mattatoio Testaccio, Rome, Italy, October 11, 2002, curated by Cristiana Perrella.\r\nNuovo spazio italiano / New Italian Space, Galleria Civica di Arte Contemporanea, Trento and Palazzo delle Albere – MART Museo d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea di Trento e Rovereto, Trento, Italy, December 7, 2002 – February 23, 2003, curated by Fabio Cavallucci, Giovanna Nicoletti, and Giorgio Verzotti. Catalogue.\r\nIronie, territorialité, stupeur, Teatro al Parco, Parma, Italy, December 17, 2002. Video program curated by Manuela Corti, in the context of Stanze aperte: Parma Poesia Open Festival, curated by Daniela Rossi, Parma, December 17–22, 2002.\r\n\r\n<strong>2003</strong>\r\nSpécial Dédicace, Musée départemental d’art contemporain de Rochechouart, Rochechouart, France, March 21 – August, 31, 2003, curated by Saâdane Afif and Mathieu Mercier.\r\nHaluk Akakce, Roberto Cuoghi, Anna Gaskell, Christian Holstad, Raymond Pettibon, David Shrigley, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, from April 16, 2003.\r\nCover Theory: L’arte contemporanea come re-interpretazione, Officina della luce, ex Centrale Emilia, Piacenza, Italy, May 11 – June 29, 2003, curated by Marco Senaldi. Catalogue.\r\nCosì va il mondo, Fondation d’Entreprise Ricard, Paris, France, June 3–27, 2003, curated by Charlotte Laubard.\r\n2003 Summer Program, Apexart, New York, USA, June 25 – July 26, 2003, organized by Katy Siegel with Michele Maccarone and Mitchell Algus. Brochure.\r\nCynical Culture, Galerie Schüppenhauer, Cologne, Germany, November 7 – December 20, 2003, curated by Steven Rand.\r\nFuori Uso 2003: Great Expectations!, Ferrotel, Pescara, Italy, November 29, 2003 – January 9, 2004, curated by Charlotte Laubard, Chiara Parisi, Alessandro Rabottini, and Marcello Smarrelli. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2004</strong>\r\nPerspectif cinema 2003–2004, Centre Georges Pompidou, Paris, France, January 29, 2004. Video program.\r\nI Nuovi Mostri, a poster project by Fondazione Nicola Trussardi, Milan, Italy, February – March, 2004, curated by Massimiliano Gioni. Catalogue.\r\n[Traveled to Venice, September 2004.]\r\nParadiso e Inferno, Fondazione Bevilacqua La Masa, Venice, Italy, May 7 – August 23, 2004, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio. Catalogue.\r\nVernice: Sentieri della giovane pittura italiana / Vernice: Pathways Through Young Italian Painting, Villa Manin Centro d’Arte Contemporanea, Passariano (Udine), Italy, May 30 – November 7, 2004, curated by Francesco Bonami and Sarah Cosulich Canarutto. Catalogue.\r\nMediterraneans: Arte Contemporanea, MACRO al Mattatoio, Rome, Italy, June 3 – September 19, 2004.\r\nAfter School Special, Ex scuole comunali, Locarno, Switzerland, August 3–14, 2004, curated by Cristina Del Ponte, Riccardo Lisi, and Noah Stolz.\r\nDimensione follia: Soggettività, passione ed eccesso nella quotidianità, Galleria Civica di Arte Contemporanea, Trento, Italy, September 24, 2004 – January 9, 2005, curated by Roberto Pinto.\r\nXI Esposizione nazionale d’arte: Artisti per Epicentro, Museo Epicentro – Arte contemporanea su mattonelle, Barcellona Pozzo di Gotto (Messina), Italy, December 12–31, 2004, curated by Nino Abbate. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\nFuori tema, Italian Feeling, XIV Quadriennale d’arte, Galleria Nazionale d’Arte Moderna, Rome, Italy, March 9 – May 31, 2005. Catalogue.\r\nI Still Believe in Miracles: Dessins sans papier, ARC – Musée d’Art Moderne de la Ville de Paris, Paris, France, April 7 – May 7, 2005, curated by Laurence Bossé, Anne Dressen, Hans Ulrich Obrist, and Angeline Scherf. Catalogue.\r\nStrata: Difference and Repetition, Fondazione Davide Halevim, Milan, Italy, May 27 – July 2, 2005, curated by Edoardo Gnemmi.\r\nChanges of Mind: Belief and Trans