no Gioni. (Conceived for this project, the work was presented on a double page of the newspaper Der Standard, Vienna, December 27, 1999).\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>2002</strong>\nDaily News, New York’s Hometown Newspaper, project curated by Aleksandra Mir, New York, USA, September 11, 2002.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>2005</strong>\n<em>The Addiction</em>, November 1–22, 2005, Gagosian Gallery, Berlin, curated by Anna-Catharina Gebbers. Presented in the context of the 4th Berlin Biennale, the exhibition brought together private collections of various artists, including some preserved sea animals from Cuoghi’s collection.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>2010</strong>\nKINDERAMA, project by Roberto Cuoghi, commissioned by the DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece. Developed during the exhibition A Guest + A Host = A Ghost, held at the DESTE Foundation in Athens from May 7 to December 31, 2009, it took the form of a 3D stereoscopic viewer loaded with photographs of children interacting with the exhibited works. KINDERAMA was presented during the exhibition Skin Fruit at the New Museum in New York, USA, from March 3 to June 6, 2010.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>2011</strong>\n<em>Solid Void</em>, Progetto Diogene, Turin, Italy, November, 7–13, 2011. Workshop curated by Roberto Cuoghi and Gian Antonio Gilli.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>2013</strong>\n<em>Arimortis</em>, Museo del Novecento, Milan, Italy, April 5 – September 8, 2013, group exhibition curated by Roberto Cuoghi and Milovan Farronato, in collaboration with DOCVA Documentation Center for Visual Arts.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>2015</strong>\n<em>Ametria</em>, Benaki Museum, Pireos St., Athens, Greece, June 12 – October 11, 2015, curated by Nicoletta De Rosa, Polina Kosmadaki, Alessandro Pasini, Tomaso Piantini, and Yorgos Tzirtzilakis. Group exhibition based on an idea by Roberto Cuoghi, organized by the DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art in collaboration with the Benaki Museum.', 'Exhi & Bio', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', 