('788', '1', '2018-11-18 22:29:26', '2018-11-18 21:29:26', 'Roberto Cuoghi (Modena, 1973). Lives and works in Milan, Italy\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>SOLO EXHIBITIONS</h2>\r\n<strong>1997</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi / Alberta Pellacani</em>, Spazio Aperto, GAM – Galleria d’Arte Moderna di Bologna, Bologna, Italy, December 19, 1997 – January 7, 1998, curated by Walter Guadagnini and Dede Auregli.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2003</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi: Foolish Things</em>, Eldorado project room, GAMeC – Galleria d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, February 9 – March 30, 2003, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio and Alessandro Rabottini.\r\n\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi</em>, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 29 – October 30, 2003.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\n<em>The Wrong Gallery</em>, New York, USA, March 7–30, 2005, curated by Maurizio Cattelan, Massimiliano Gioni, and Ali Subotnick.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2006</strong>\r\n<em>Mei Gui</em>, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 22 – October 4, 2006.\r\n\r\n<em>Mbube</em>, objectif_exhibitions, Antwerp, Belgium, October 26 – November 25, 2006, curated by Tommy Simoens.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2007</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi: Mei Gui</em>, Centre International d’Art et du Paysage de l’Île de Vassivière, Beaumont du Lac, France, January 17, 2007. Presented in the context of Un million et quarante-quatrième anniversaire de l’art / 1 000 044 candles for art, held on January 17 in various venues throughout France.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2008</strong>\r\n<em>Suillakku</em>, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, May 6 – July 27, 2008, curated by M. Beccaria.\r\n[Traveled to ICA – Institute of Contemporary Arts, London, UK, October 14 – November 23, 2008].\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2011</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi</em>, UCLA Hammer Museum, Los Angeles, USA, January 22 – May 15, 2011, curated by Ali Subotnick.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2012</strong>\r\n<em>ZOLOTO</em>, Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, May 30 – July 13, 2012.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2014</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi: Suillakku Corral</em>, New Museum, New York, USA, April 30 – June 29, 2014, curated by Massimiliano Gioni and Margot Norton.\r\n\r\n<em>Da iḍā e piṅgalā a iḍā e iḍā o piṅgalā e piṅgalā</em>, Le Consortium, centre d’art, Dijon, France, October 17, 2014 – January 11, 2015.\r\n[Traveled to Aspen Art Museum, Aspen, USA, February 13 – May 31, 2015].\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2016</strong>\r\n<em>Putiferio</em>, DESTE Foundation Project Space, Slaughterhouse, Hydra, Greece, June 21 – September 30, 2016.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2017</strong>\r\n<em>Roberto Cuoghi: Perla Pollina, 1996–2016</em>, Centre d’Art Contemporain Genève, Geneva, Switzerland, February 22 – April 30, 2017, curated by Andrea Bellini.                                                                                                                                                                              [Traveling to Madre – Museo d’arte contemporanea Donnaregina, Naples, Italy, May 15 – September 11, 2017].\r\n\r\n<em>Imitazione di Cristo (Imitation of Christ)</em>; “Il Mondo Magico” (The Magical World), Italian Pavilion, 57° Biennale di Venezia, Venice, Italy, May 13 – November 26, curated by Cecilia Alemani.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>GROUP EXHIBITIONS</h2>\r\n<strong>1996</strong>\r\n<em>Orizzontale verticale: Giovani artisti modenesi, 1a edizione</em>, Palazzo della Provincia, Modena, Italy, December 14, 1996 – January 25, 1997, curated by Roberto Daolio and Corrado Levi.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>1997</strong>\r\n<em>Menotrenta: 2a selezione di giovani artisti</em>, Spazio Laboratorio Hajech, Milan, Italy, February 11 – March 8, 1997, curated by Francesca Pensa and Francesco Tedeschi.\r\n\r\n<em>LAB.12.2 - T.I.N.A. (there is no alternative)</em>, Viafarini, Milan, Italy, April 18 – May 2, 1997, curated by R. Daolio.\r\n\r\n<em>Conversazione in giardino</em>, Orto Botanico, Ferrara, Italy, September 27 – October 19, 1997, curated by Gilberto Pellizzola.\r\n\r\n<em>Raccolta del disegno contemporaneo: Nuove acquisizioni 1994–1997</em>, Palazzina dei Giardini, Modena, Italy, November 30, 1997 – January 25, 1998, curated by Claudia Zanfi.\r\n\r\n<em>Visual Rave</em>, La Società Umanitaria, Milan, Italy, December 12, 1997 – January 12, 1998, curated by Antonio d’Avossa and Centro Arte a Parte.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>1999</strong>\r\n<em>Fine</em>, Studio Armin Linke, Milan, Italy, May 31 – June 18, 1999, curated by Lorenzo Silvan.\r\n\r\n<em>Guarene Arte 99</em>, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo per l’Arte, September 25 – November 7, 1999, Guarene d’Alba (Cuneo), Italy, selected by Emanuela De Cecco.\r\n\r\n<em>In Camera Caritatis</em>, Globale Positionen 10, Museum in Progress, Vienna, Austria, curated by Massimiliano Gioni.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2000</strong>\r\n<em>3nds: Milano</em>, Salara, Bologna, Italy, May 19 – June 13, 2000, curated by Alessandra Galasso and Gianfranco Maraniello.\r\n\r\n<em>Fuori Uso 2000. The Bridges: Art on the highway / Arte in autostrada</em>, Lungo fiume sud, Pescara, Italy, July 2–19, 2000, curated by Helena Kontova, Emanuela De Cecco, Hou Hanru, and Andreas Schlaegel &amp; Angela Rosenberg.\r\n\r\n<em>Fai da te / The Amateur View</em>, Sparwasser HQ, Berlin, Germany, December 8, 2000 – January, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2001</strong>\r\n<em>Primo piano: Su la testa! Opere e argomenti in scena</em>, Palazzo delle Papesse Centro Arte Contemporanea, Siena, Italy, February 4–11, 2001, curated by Sergio Risaliti.\r\n\r\n<em>Magic and Loss in Pandæmonium: Biennial of Moving Images 2001</em>, The Lux Centre, London, UK, March 2 – April 8, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza and Cristiana Perrella.\r\n[The exhibition was also presented at Artistinvetrina, Fendissime, Rome, Italy, March 2–6, 2001, in collaboration with The British School at Rome; CAC Contemporary Art Centre, Vilnius, Lithuania, March 21 – April 15, 2001: Magic &amp; Loss: Video by young Italian artists, MAN – Museo d’Arte Provincia di Nuoro, Nuoro, Italy, April 6 – May 6, 2001: Magic and Loss: Contemporary Italian Video].\r\n\r\n<em>Play &gt;</em>, Openspace, Milan, Italy, March 28 – April 29, 2001, curated by Gigiotto del Vecchio.\r\n\r\n<em>Espresso: Arte oggi in Italia</em>, Manifattura Tabacchi, Florence, Italy, June 10 – July 20, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza and Gianfranco Maraniello. The exhibition was part of Boom!, a program of five exhibitions curated by Sergio Risaliti.\r\n\r\n<em>Il dono: Offerta, ospitalità, insidia / The Gift: Generous Offerings, Threatening Hospitality</em>, Palazzo delle Papesse Centro Arte Contemporanea, Siena, Italy, June 2 – September 23, 2001, curated by Gianfranco Maraniello, Sergio Risaliti, and Antonio Somaini, organized by ICI – Independent Curators International.\r\n[Traveled to Centro Culturale Candiani, Mestre (Venice), Italy, October 14, 2001 – January 6, 2002; Scottsdale Museum of Contemporary Art, Scottsdale, USA, February 7 – May 5, 2002; Bronx Museum of the Arts, Bronx, USA, November 27, 2002 – March 2, 2003; Mary and Leigh Block Museum of Art, Northwestern University, Evanston, USA, April 4 – June 22, 2003; Art Gallery of Hamilton, Hamilton, Canada, August 9 – October 18, 2003].\r\n\r\n<em>Videorom in The 1st Valencia Biennial: Communication between the Arts</em>, various venues, Valencia, Spain, June 13 – October 20, 2001, curated by Cristiana Perrella.\r\n\r\n<em>The End of All Things</em>, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, from June 20, 2001.\r\n\r\n<em>Tirana Biennale 1: Escape</em>, National Gallery and Chinese Pavilion, Tirana, Albania, September 15 – October 15, 2001, invited by Jens Hoffmann.\r\n\r\n<em>In fumo: Arte, fumetto, comunicazione / In fumo: Art, comics, communication</em>, GAMeC – Galleria d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea di Bergamo, Bergamo, Italy, September 27, 2001 – January 6, 2002, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2002</strong>\r\n<em>Manifesta 4: European Biennial of Contemporary Art</em>, various venues, Frankfurt, Germany, May 25 – August 25, 2002, curated by Iara Boubnova, Nuria Enguita Mayo, and Stéphanie Moisdon Trembley.\r\n\r\n<em>Verso il futuro: Identità nell’arte italiana 1990–2002</em>, Museo del Corso, Rome, Italy, June 26 – August 25, 2002, curated by Costantino D’Orazio and Ludovico Pratesi.\r\n\r\n<em>ExIt: Nuove geografie della creatività italiana</em>, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, September 21, 2002 – January 6, 2003, curated by Francesco Bonami.\r\n\r\n<em>Polyphonix 40</em>, Centre Georges Pompidou, Paris, France, October 1–10, 2002, curated by Manuela Corti.\r\n\r\n<em>VideoROM 4.0</em>, ex Mattatoio Testaccio, Rome, Italy, October 11, 2002, curated by Cristiana Perrella.\r\n\r\n<em>Nuovo spazio italiano / New Italian Space</em>, Galleria Civica di Arte Contemporanea, Trento and Palazzo delle Albere – MART Museo d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea di Trento e Rovereto, Trento, Italy, December 7, 2002 – February 23, 2003, curated by Fabio Cavallucci, Giovanna Nicoletti, and Giorgio Verzotti.\r\n\r\n<em>Ironie, territorialité, stupeur</em>, Teatro al Parco, Parma, Italy, December 17, 2002. Video program curated by Manuela Corti, in the context of Stanze aperte: Parma Poesia Open Festival, curated by Daniela Rossi, Parma, December 17–22, 2002.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2003</strong>\r\n<em>Spécial Dédicace</em>, Musée départemental d’art contemporain de Rochechouart, Rochechouart, France, March 21 – August, 31, 2003, curated by Saâdane Afif and Mathieu Mercier.\r\n\r\n<em>Haluk Akakce, Roberto Cuoghi, Anna Gaskell, Christian Holstad, Raymond Pettibon, David Shrigley</em>, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, from April 16, 2003.\r\n\r\n<em>Cover Theory: L’arte contemporanea come re-interpretazione</em>, Officina della luce, ex Centrale Emilia, Piacenza, Italy, May 11 – June 29, 2003, curated by Marco Senaldi.\r\n\r\n<em>Così va il mondo</em>, Fondation d’Entreprise Ricard, Paris, France, June 3–27, 2003, curated by Charlotte Laubard.\r\n\r\n<em>2003 Summer Program</em>, Apexart, New York, USA, June 25 – July 26, 2003, organized by Katy Siegel with Michele Maccarone and Mitchell Algus.\r\n\r\n<em>Cynical Culture</em>, Galerie Schüppenhauer, Cologne, Germany, November 7 – December 20, 2003, curated by Steven Rand.\r\n\r\n<em>Fuori Uso 2003: Great Expectations!</em>, Ferrotel, Pescara, Italy, November 29, 2003 – January 9, 2004, curated by Charlotte Laubard, Chiara Parisi, Alessandro Rabottini, and Marcello Smarrelli.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2004</strong>\r\n<em>Perspectif cinema 2003–2004</em>, Centre Georges Pompidou, Paris, France, January 29, 2004. Video program.\r\n\r\n<em>I Nuovi Mostri</em>, a poster project by Fondazione Nicola Trussardi, Milan, Italy, February – March, 2004, curated by Massimiliano Gioni. [Traveled to Venice, September 2004].\r\n\r\n<em>Paradiso e Inferno</em>, Fondazione Bevilacqua La Masa, Venice, Italy, May 7 – August 23, 2004, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio.\r\n\r\n<em>Vernice: Sentieri della giovane pittura italiana / Vernice: Pathways Through Young Italian Painting</em>, Villa Manin Centro d’Arte Contemporanea, Passariano (Udine), Italy, May 30 – November 7, 2004, curated by Francesco Bonami and Sarah Cosulich Canarutto.\r\n\r\n<em>Mediterraneans: Arte Contemporanea</em>, MACRO al Mattatoio, Rome, Italy, June 3 – September 19, 2004.\r\n\r\n<em>After School Special</em>, Ex scuole comunali, Locarno, Switzerland, August 3–14, 2004, curated by Cristina Del Ponte, Riccardo Lisi, and Noah Stolz.\r\n\r\n<em>Dimensione follia: Soggettività, passione ed eccesso nella quotidianità</em>, Galleria Civica di Arte Contemporanea, Trento, Italy, September 24, 2004 – January 9, 2005, curated by Roberto Pinto.\r\n\r\n<em>XI Esposizione nazionale d’arte: Artisti per Epicentro</em>, Museo Epicentro – Arte contemporanea su mattonelle, Barcellona Pozzo di Gotto (Messina), Italy, December 12–31, 2004, curated by Nino Abbate.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\n<em>Fuori tema, Italian Feeling</em>, XIV Quadriennale d’arte, Galleria Nazionale d’Arte Moderna, Rome, Italy, March 9 – May 31, 2005.\r\n\r\n<em>I Still Believe in Miracles: Dessins sans papier</em>, ARC – Musée d’Art Moderne de la Ville de Paris, Paris, France, April 7 – May 7, 2005, curated by Laurence Bossé, Anne Dressen, Hans Ulrich Obrist, and Angeline Scherf.\r\n\r\n<em>Strata: Difference and Repetition</em>, Fondazione Davide Halevim, Milan, Italy, May 27 – July 2, 2005, curated by Edoardo Gnemmi.\r\n\r\n<em>Changes of Mind: Belief and Transformation</em>, Haunch of Venison, London, UK, July 7 – August 25, 2005.\r\n\r\n<em>Videominuto Pop TV</em>, Centro per l’Arte Contemporanea Luigi Pecci, Prato, PAN Palazzo delle Arti di Napoli, Naples, and Enzimi: Festival della creatività contemporanea, Castel Porziano beach (Rome), Italy, September, 8–10, 2005.\r\n\r\n<em>The IX Baltic Triennial of International Art</em> – BMW, Contemporary Art Center, Vilnius, Lithuania, September 23 – November 20, 2005, curated by Sofia Hernández Chong Cuy, Raimundas Malašauskas, and Alexis Vaillant.\r\n\r\n<em>La linea sottile, logiche dell’invisibile</em>, Museo Laboratorio, Città Sant’Angelo (Pescara), Italy, October 22 – November 20, 2005, curated by Marco Antonini and Francesca Colasante.\r\n\r\n<em>La sindrome di Pantagruel</em>, T1 Torino Triennale Tremusei, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, and GAM – Galleria Civica d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea, Turin, Italy, November 9, 2005 – March 19, 2006, curated by Francesco Bonami and Carolyn Christov-Bakargiev.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2006</strong>\r\n<em>Villa Jelmini: The Complex of Respect</em>, Kunsthalle Bern, Bern, Switzerland, January 28 – March 26, 2006, curated by Philippe Pirotte. (For this occasion, a facsimile edition of the catalogue originally published in conjunction with the show Live in Your Head: When Attitudes Become Form, curated by Harald Szeemann in 1969, was reprinted.)\r\n\r\n<em>EGOmania: Just When I Think I’ve Understood... / Appena ho capito d’aver capito...</em>, Galleria Civica di Modena and Palazzo Santa Margherita – Palazzina dei Giardini, Modena, Italy, January ,29 – May 2, 2006, curated by Milovan Farronato.\r\n\r\n<em>Panic Room: Works from the Dakis Joannou Collection</em>, DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece, February 2, 2006 – April 4, 2007, curated by Jeffrey Deitch and Kathy Grayson.\r\n\r\n<em>Biennale Cuvée 06: World Selection of Contemporary Art</em>, OK Centrum für Gegenwartskunst, Linz, Austria, February 10 – April 9, 2006, curated by Genoveva Rückert and Martin Sturm. Ecce Uomo: (33+1) artisti contemporanei da collezioni private a Milano, Spazio Oberdan, Milan, Italy, March 23 – May 21, 2006, curated by Gemma De Angelis Testa and Sergio Risaliti.\r\n\r\n<em>Von Mäusen und Menschen / Of Mice and Men</em>, 4th Berlin Biennale for Contemporary Art, various venues, Berlin, Germany, March 25 – June 5, 2006, curated by Maurizio Cattelan, Massimiliano ,Gioni, and Ali Subotnick.\r\n\r\n<em>Elettroshock: Il video in Italia dagli anni ‘70 a oggi (1973–2006)</em>, Central Academy of Fine Arts, ,Beijing and Guangdong Museum of Art, Guangzhou, China, March 25–26 and April 1–2, 2006, curated by Bruno Di Marino and Lara Nicoli.\r\n\r\n<em>Il buco</em>, Galleria Pio Monti, Rome, Italy, May 13–30, 2006, curated by Achille Bonito Oliva.\r\n\r\n<em>Il Museo Insostenibile</em>, La Rada, Locarno, Switzerland, April 8–9, 2006, curated by Noah Stolz.\r\n\r\n<em>Supernova: Experience Pommery #3</em>, Domaine Pommery, Reims, France, May 12 – October 31, ,2006, curated by Judicaël Lavrador. (A special issue of Beaux Arts Magazine was devoted to the exhibition).\r\n\r\n<em>Young Italian Artists at the Turn of the Millennium</em>, Galleria Continua, Beijing, China, July 1 – ,August 20, 2006.\r\n\r\n<em>Frame: A Selection of Italian Artists</em>, Gertrude Contemporary Art Spaces, Melbourne, Australia, August 25 – September 23, 2006, curated by Chiara Agnello and Roberta Tenconi. The exhibition was part of M.M.M. (milano.melbourne.milano), a cultural exchange project between the cities of Milan and Melbourne.\r\n\r\n<em>A Secret Service: Art, Compulsion, Concealment</em>, Hatton Gallery, Newcastle, UK, September 17 – November 11, 2006, a Hayward Gallery Touring Exhibition, curated by Richard Grayson.\r\n[Traveled to De La Warr Pavilion, Bexhill on Sea, UK, January 27 – April 15, 2007; Whitworth Art Gallery, Manchester, UK, May 5 – August 5, 2007].\r\n\r\n<em>CerealArt</em>, NADA Art Fair, Miami, USA, December 6–10, 2006. Presentation of the works previously exhibited at The Wrong Gallery, New York, USA, in a 1:6 scale version. Cuoghi participated with a miniaturized version of F(IIA)l, 2005.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>2007</strong>\r\n<em>Our Magic Hour: European artists’ show</em>, Arario Gallery, Cheonan, South Korea, January 26 – March 11, 2007, curated by Milovan Farronato.\r\n\r\n<em>I Want to Believe</em>, Galerie Eva Presenhuber, Zurich, Switzerland, March 3 – April 7, 2007, curated by Milovan Farronato.\r\n\r\n<em>Dalla terra alla luna: Metafore di viaggio (parte I e II) / From the Earth to the Moon: Metaphors for Travel (Part I and II)</em>, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, April 4 – August 26, 2007, curated by Marcella Beccaria.\r\n\r\n<em>Sequence 1: Pittura e scultura nella Collezione François Pinault / Sequence 1: Peinture et sculpture dans la Collection François Pinault</em>, Palazzo Grassi, Venice, Italy, May 5 – November 11, 2007, curated by Alison M. Gingeras.\r\n\r\n<em>Où? Scènes du Sud: Espagne, Italie, Portugal</em>, Carré d’Art – Musée d’Art Contemporain de Nîmes, Nîmes, F