('1173', '1', '2019-02-06 19:15:39', '2019-02-06 18:15:39', '<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">General Inquries:</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"mailto:info@robertocuoghi.com\">info@robertocuoghi.com</a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">Note to collectors:</h2>\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":35,\"className\":\"viewmore_btn\"} -->\n<div style=\"height:35px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer viewmore_btn\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\",\"className\":\"viewmore_txt\"} -->\n<p style=\"text-align:center\" class=\"viewmore_txt\">Roberto Cuoghi’s Retrobalera Studio is working on the issue of new Certificates of Authenticity to replace the ones previously given out by the Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Lehmann Maupin Gallery and Galerie Chantal Crousel.<br><br>The new certificates should accompany the artworks if they are sold or their ownership transferred by any other means, as they are the only official documents attesting to their authenticity.<br><br>The website <a href=\"https://www.robertocuoghi.com/\">robertocuoghi.com</a> lists the works recognized as authentic by the artist’s studio. The locations of some of them are no longer known.<br><br>Anyone owning a work whose location is no longer known or who wishes to receive a new certificate is kindly requested to email us at <a href=\"mailto:certificates@robertocuoghi.com\">certificates@robertocuoghi.com</a><br><br>All information associated with the ownership of artworks listed in the web archive is strictly confidential.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Contact', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '748-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-02-06 19:15:39', '2019-02-06 18:15:39', '', '748', 'https://www.robertocuoghi.com/748-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
